Roles & Permissions Setup
Roles & Permissions Definition:
Admin: Full permissions (View/Write on Projects, Bookings, Techs, CMS, and User Management).
Moderator: Read/Write permissions on Projects, Bookings, Techs. Restricted/hidden access to User Management and CMS edit operations.
Viewer: Read-only access to all sections. Can search/filter, but cannot save, edit, or delete items.
User Management Extension:
Add a Role selector dropdown (Admin, Moderator, Viewer) when creating system users.
In AdminPage.jsx, intercept all submit handlers (projects, techs, bookings status, CMS saving, user additions/deletions) to block actions if the logged-in user's role doesn't have the appropriate clearance.
Render visually locked indicators (e.g., lock icon 🔒, disabled save buttons, and helper banners) if the current user's role has insufficient permissions.

